<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11125i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11125i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11125i"> 125(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lafayette (C&eacute;sar-Gille) / ape</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>La Fayette</b> En cette ann&eacute;e 1834, M. de <mark>la Fayette</mark> vient de mourir. J&apos;aurais jadis &eacute;t&eacute; injuste en parlant de lui; je l&apos;aurais repr&eacute;sent&eacute; comme une esp&egrave;ce de niais &agrave; double visage et &agrave; deux renomm&eacute;es; <mark>h&eacute;ros de l&apos;autre c&ocirc;t&eacute; de l&apos;Atlantique, Gille de ce c&ocirc;t&eacute;-ci</mark>. <br>[In this year 1834, Mr de la Fayette has just died. Formerly I would have been unjust in talking of him; I would have represented him as a duplicitous fool with two reputations: a hero on the other side of the Atlantic, a Gille on this side. <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 181</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: &ldquo;C&eacute;sar-Gille&rdquo; is in fact Rivarol&apos;s epigram. A Gille is a stage simpleton; also the name of an ape in the source. </mm> </dd></dl>
